{
  "text": "We did not find any flow velocity variables other than DSVR that correlated significantly with the change in RWM or with the change in EF. Several factors have been proposed as determinants of the absolute blood flow values in the infarct area, including collateral circulation [CITATION_1] , severity of stenosis (16), viscosity of blood, flow reserve capacity (17), preload and afterload [CITATION_2] and the extent of the reperfusion injury and of \"no reflow\" phenomenon [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Therefore, it is difficult to evaluate the microvascular flow to the myocardium from the absolute values of the coronary flow velocity alone.",
